                     <binding notAfter="1500" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>15th century, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName> (same as manuscript): severe damp damage, 
                           ? from immersion; pasteboards (probably late replacements); original cover of dark brown leather, blind-tooled 
                           with multiple lines, tools, dots and strapwork; spine lost; no clear surviving evidence of clasps, unless possibly 
                           of a central strap-and-pin fastening; outlines of a small circular metal fitting at the centre of each cover; edges plain, 
                           distorted. Heavily repaired with reback in lighter brown leather and probably new boards, late 19th century, Bodleian</p>
                     </binding>
